Programming Assignment 6

Short Description:
This program makes use of a Big Integer ADT created in C++ to perform calculations on large integers.

Build:
A Makefile is provided and can be used to build the program. This can be accomplished within the directory where the program files are located by typing 'make Arithmetic'. 

Running:
The format for running Arithmetic <input file> <output file>

Cleaning:
To remove all files that were generated by the compiler, type the command 'make clean’.

FILES-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Arithmetic.cpp:
Program used to read in and output calculations performed big integers 

BigInteger.cpp:
Source file containing the implementation of the Big Integer ADT

BigInteger.h:
Header file containing function prototypes for the Big Integer ADT

BigIntegerTest.cpp:
File containing thorough testing of the Big Integer ADT

List.cpp:
Source file containing the implementation of the List ADT

List.h:
Header file containing function prototypes for the List ADT

ListTest.cpp:
File containing thorough testing of the List ADT

Makefile:
File that creates an executable binary file called Arithmetic 

README:
File displaying contents of PA6 and any other messages for graders

